        " consulting rooms with Joness sister, Elizabeth, installed as housekeeper. Trotter and Elizabeth Jones later married. Appalled by the treatment of the mentally ill in institutions, Jones began experimenting with hypnotic techniques in his clinical work.     Jones first encountered Freuds writings directly in 42 in a German psychiatric journal in which Freud published the famous ": null
