        ", where Freud gave a series of lectures on psychoanalysis, and in the Netherlands the following year, Jones set about forging strong working relationships with the nascent American psychoanalytic movement. He gave some 42 papers or addresses to American professional societies at venues ranging from Boston, to Washington and Chicago. In 42 he co-founded the American Psychopathological Association and the following year the ": null
