        " analysts. It was agreed further that all the key policy making committees of the BPS should have representatives from the three groups. Baker, Ron ‘The evolution of organisational and training procedures in psychoanalytic associations: a brief account of the unique British contribution’ in Johns, J. and Steiner, R. Within Time and Beyond Time: A Festschrift for Pearl King, London: Karnac, 42 pp. 42–42       After the end of the war, Jones gradually relinquished his many official posts whilst continuing his psychoanalytic practice, writings and lecturing. The major undertaking of his final years was his monumental account of Freuds life and work, published to widespread acclaim in three volumes between 42 and 42 In this he was ably assisted by his German-speaking wife, who translated much of Freuds early correspondence and other archive documentation made available by ": null
    },
